properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Control - COBAKI LAKES M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland Government has implemented enhanced border control measures, including border passes and identification screening.

Any person that has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. All of Victoria and Greater Sydney are currently declared COVID-19 hotspots. From 1am Saturday 8 August, all local government areas in NSW and ACT will also be declared COVID-19 hotspots.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW at this 24/7 checkpoint must hold a valid Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

Pass holders should allow plenty of additional travel time to cross the NSW-Queensland border, particularly during peak periods.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail Project - PARRAMATTA Harris St between George Street AND Hassall Street
properties.diversions:
The following changed traffic conditions are now in place:

  • The southbound carriageway has been reduced to one lane.
  • Motorists on Harris St northbound must turn left into Hassall St.
  • Motorists on MacArthur St southbound are now able to turn right into George St westbound. 
  • There is no through access on Hassall St eastbound between Wigram St and Harris St.
  • Motorists on Hassall St eastbound must turn right into Wigram St.

At this stage, these changes will remain in place until at least the end of the year.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail Project

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - PARRAMATTA Macquarie St between Harris Street AND Marsden Street
properties.otherAdvice:
The following changed traffic conditions are now in place:

  • Macquarie St has been reduced to one westbound lane.
  • The right turn from Charles St to Macquarie St westbound has been restricted.
  • The right turn from Macquarie St into Horwood Pl has also been restricted. Motorists can instead use George St to access Horwood Pl.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - BANKSTOWN Stacey Street between Macauley Avenue AND Stanley Street/Salvia Avenue
properties.otherAdvice:
Work is taking place to construct a third northbound lane on Stacey St.

Southbound carriageway: lanes 1 and 2 will carry southbound traffic, and lane 3 will carry northbound traffic.

Northbound carriageway: lane 1 is closed and 2 is open. Northbound traffic will also use a contained southbound lane under contraflow conditions. 3.5m width restrictions wide loads to use lane 2 (fast lane) northbound.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - WESTMEAD Hawkesbury Road between Darcy Road AND Hainsworth Street
properties.otherAdvice:
• Hawkesbury Rd, between Darcy Rd and Queens Rd, has reopened to two way traffic.
  • Hawkesbury Rd, between Queens Rd and Hainsworth St, is now one-way northbound.
  • Hainsworth St, between Hawkesbury Rd and Park Ave, is now one-way eastbound.
  • There will be no left turn from Hainsworth St into Hawkesbury Rd for southbound traffic.
  • These traffic changes will remain until 2023, when Parramatta Light Rail will commence operation.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Oversize vehicles - MOUNT VICTORIA Great Western Highway to River Lett Hill
properties.otherAdvice:
A series of 70m-long loads will travel down Victoria Pass and up River Lett Hill early each morning. For the safety of motorists, changed traffic conditions will be in place.

Eastbound traffic will be held at River Lett Hill and the bottom of Mount Victoria while the trucks use these sections of road. Traffic will be stopped for 20-25 minutes between 4am and 5am.

Westbound motorists will experience delays while following the oversize vehicles because they will need to travel at low speed through this section.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - PARRAMATTA Church Street between Factory Street, North Parramatta AND Macquarie Street
properties.otherAdvice:
The following changed traffic conditions are in place until the operational launch of the Parramatta Light Rail:

  • Church St is closed to traffic in both directions.
  • There is no access to Church Street from the eastern side of Albert Street.
  • There is no access to Church Street from the western side of Factory, Harold, Fennell and Ross Streets.
properties.diversions:
Motorists are encouraged to use OConnell Street to travel across
Parramatta during this time.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Control - TIBOOBURRA Fortville Gate Road at Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland Government has implemented enhanced border control measures, including border passes and identification screening.

Any person who has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. From 1am Thursday 1 October, the NSW border zone has been extended; see the Queensland government website for more information.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW must complete a Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

  • This border control point is accessible via a coded lock.
  • Declaration pass holders must call the new Border Control phone number 0417 385 112 between 8am and 4pm Monday to Friday for the code to gate.
  • Pass holders should call in advance due to a lack of mobile phone reception at the border control point.

properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets - THE ROCKS George St between Hickson Rd AND Lower Fort St
properties.otherAdvice:
Long term special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on George St in The Rocks to accommodate the weekly Rocks Markets.

Clearways will be in effect every weekend from 10pm Friday until 10pm Sunday on the eastern side of George St between Hickson Rd and Lower Fort St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

Road closures will also be in place on weekends for the markets from 4am Saturday until 10pm Sunday on sections on Argyle St, Artherden St, George St, Kendall Lane, Mill Lane and Playfair St.
properties.displayName: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets
